{
  "texts": [
    "We adapt the same optimiser, learning_rate and warmup_steps as Taori et al. (2023), and set these to adamw, 3 × 10 -4 and 100, respectively.",
    "We use Low Rank Adaptation to reduce the number of trainable parameters and similar to Taori et al. (2023) set the rank and alpha hyper-parameters to 16, dropout to 0.05 and target the q_proj, k_proj, v_proj, and o_proj modules of the base model.",
    "This reduces the trainable parameters to 26,214,400 or 0.2% of the base model.",
    "The final models are trained for 5 epochs totalling 1,200 steps.",
    "Training hardware."
  ]
}